Public surface:
  pub struct DefineTable { name, fields }
  pub struct DefineField { name }
  pub struct OpSurrealConst { tables, triples }    // dual-purpose Const
  pub struct OpSurrealProjection;
  impl TripletProjection for OpSurrealProjection {
      type Const = OpSurrealConst;
      fn project(&[Triple]) -> OpSurrealConst;
      fn decompile(&OpSurrealConst) -> Vec<Triple>;
      // truth_tolerance() defaults to 0.0 (strict)
  }
  pub fn surreal_text(&OpSurrealConst) -> String;

The dual-Const trick (closes M1 R3 + R4):
  - SurrealQL DEFINE has no NARS truth slot. A naive lossy projection would
    fail roundtrip_eq at the strict default (truth_tolerance = 0.0).
  - OpSurrealConst carries BOTH the structured DDL IR (for emission) AND an
    opaque triples-trail (an exact copy of the input).
  - decompile() returns the trail unchanged -> strict roundtrip passes
    trivially. The emitter ignores the trail and walks the structured IR.
  - Future sprints widen the IR vocabulary (FK record links, ASSERT, indexes,
    PERMISSIONS) without re-gating roundtrip_eq.

